            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingCardio">
                <button class="accordion-button" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseCardio" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="collapseCardio">
                  <i class="fas fa-running me-2 text-primary"></i> Cardiovascular Exercise
                </button>
              </h2>
              <div id="collapseCardio" class="accordion-collapse collapse show" aria-labelledby="headingCardio" data-bs-parent="#exerciseAccordion">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <p>Cardio exercises elevate your heart rate and improve cardiovascular health, endurance, and calorie burning.</p>
                  
                  <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-md-6">
                      <h6>Low-Impact Options:</h6>
                      <ul>
                        <li>Walking</li>
                        <li>Swimming</li>
                        <li>Cycling</li>
                        <li>Elliptical training</li>
                        <li>Dancing</li>
                      </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-6">
                      <h6>Higher-Impact Options:</h6>
                      <ul>
                        <li>Running</li>
                        <li>HIIT (High-Intensity Interval Training)</li>
                        <li>Kickboxing</li>
                        <li>Jump rope</li>
                        <li>Step aerobics</li>
                      </ul>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  
                  <div class="alert alert-success mt-3">
                    <strong>Pro Tip:</strong> Mix up your cardio routine to prevent boredom and exercise plateaus. Try different activities that you enjoy!
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingStrength">
                <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseStrength" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseStrength">
                  <i class="fas fa-dumbbell me-2 text-primary"></i> Strength Training
                </button>
              </h2>
              <div id="collapseStrength" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingStrength" data-bs-parent="#exerciseAccordion">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <p>Strength training is particularly important for women to maintain muscle mass, boost metabolism, and strengthen bones. Contrary to common myths, lifting weights will not make women "bulky" - it will create lean, strong muscle.</p>
                  
                  <h6 class="mt-3">Strength Training Options:</h6>
                  <ul>
                    <li><strong>Bodyweight exercises:</strong> Squats, lunges, push-ups, planks</li>
                    <li><strong>Free weights:</strong> Dumbbells, barbells, kettlebells</li>
                    <li><strong>Resistance bands:</strong> Great for home workouts and travel</li>
                    <li><strong>Weight machines:</strong> Provide guidance and support for beginners</li>
                    <li><strong>Pilates:</strong> Focuses on core strength and controlled movements</li>
                  </ul>
                  
                  <p><strong>Recommendation:</strong> Aim to work all major muscle groups (legs, hips, back, chest, abdomen, shoulders, and arms) at least twice a week.</p>
                  
                  <div class="alert alert-warning mt-3">
                    <i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle me-2"></i> Always start with lighter weights and focus on proper form to prevent injury. Consider working with a certified trainer initially.
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingFlexibility">
                <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseFlexibility" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseFlexibility">
                  <i class="fas fa-spa me-2 text-primary"></i> Flexibility & Balance
                </button>
              </h2>
              <div id="collapseFlexibility" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingFlexibility" data-bs-parent="#exerciseAccordion">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <p>Flexibility and balance exercises improve range of motion, reduce injury risk, and enhance functional movement patterns. They're especially important as women age.</p>
                  
                  <h6 class="mt-3">Recommended Activities:</h6>
                  <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-md-6">
                      <ul>
                        <li><strong>Yoga:</strong> Combines flexibility, balance, and strength</li>
                        <li><strong>Tai Chi:</strong> Gentle flowing movements that improve balance</li>
                        <li><strong>Pilates:</strong> Emphasizes core strength and controlled movement</li>
                      </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-6">
                      <ul>
                        <li><strong>Static stretching:</strong> Holding stretches for 15-60 seconds</li>
                        <li><strong>Dynamic stretching:</strong> Moving through a full range of motion</li>
                        <li><strong>Balance exercises:</strong> Single-leg stands, heel-to-toe walks</li>
                      </ul>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  
                  <p><strong>Tip:</strong> These practices are excellent for stress reduction as well, as they often incorporate mindfulness and breathwork.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingFunctional">
                <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseFunctional" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseFunctional">
                  <i class="fas fa-apple-crate me-2 text-primary"></i> Functional Fitness
                </button>
              </h2>
              <div id="collapseFunctional" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingFunctional" data-bs-parent="#exerciseAccordion">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <p>Functional fitness focuses on training your muscles to work together for daily tasks by simulating common movements you might do at home, work, or in sports.</p>
                  
                  <h6 class="mt-3">Key Benefits for Women:</h6>
                  <ul>
                    <li>Improves ability to carry groceries, lift children, and perform household tasks</li>
                    <li>Enhances posture and core strength, reducing back pain</li>
                    <li>Decreases injury risk during everyday activities</li>
                    <li>Supports independence and quality of life as you age</li>
                  </ul>
                  
                  <h6 class="mt-3">Examples of Functional Exercises:</h6>
                  <ul>
                    <li>Squat to overhead press (mimics picking something up and placing it on a shelf)</li>
                    <li>Step-ups with weight (mimics climbing stairs while carrying a load)</li>
                    <li>Medicine ball rotational throws (mimics twisting movements in daily life)</li>
                    <li>Farmer's carries (mimics carrying heavy items in each hand)</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="card mb-4">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">Exercise Through Life Stages</h5>
          
          <div class="table-responsive">
            <table class="table table-hover">
              <thead>
                <tr>
                  <th>Life Stage</th>
                  <th>Considerations</th>
                  <th>Recommended Focus</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr>
                  <td><strong>20s & 30s</strong></td>
                  <td>Building foundation for lifelong fitness; higher capacity for intensity</td>
                  <td>
                    <ul class="mb-0">
                      <li>Build bone density through weight-bearing exercise</li>
                      <li>Establish consistent exercise habits</li>
                      <li>Challenge yourself with variety</li>
                      <li>Consider training for events like 5Ks or obstacle courses</li>
                    </ul>
                  </td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><strong>During Pregnancy</strong></td>
                  <td>Adapting to changing body and energy levels</td>
                  <td>
                    <ul class="mb-0">
                      <li>Low-impact cardio like swimming and walking</li>
                      <li>Modified strength training with lighter weights</li>
                      <li>Prenatal yoga for flexibility and relaxation</li>
                      <li>Pelvic floor exercises</li>
                    </ul>
                  </td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><strong>Postpartum</strong></td>
                  <td>Recovery and rebuilding core strength</td>
